UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Wilfredo CANALES-CASTILLO, also known as Wilfredo Canales, also known as Wilfredo Villatoro-Canalez, Defendant-Appellant. No. 14-40574

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 21, 2015. Renata Ann Gowie, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Marjorie A. Meyers, Federal Public Defender, Philip G. Gallagher, H. Michael Sokolow, Assistant Federal Public Defender; Federal Public Defender’s Office, Houston, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Wilfredo Canales-Castillo, Pecos, TX, pro se. Before REAVLEY, SMITH, and GRAVES, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Wilfredo Canales-Castillo has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967), and United States v. Flores, 632 F.3d 229 (5th Cir.2011). Canales-Castillo has not filed a response. We have reviewed counsel’s brief and the relevant portions of the record reflected therein. We concur with counsel’s assessment that the appeal presents no nonfrivolous issue for appellate review. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
